column5: IWM quietest power hour

A good piece on the trends in investment management and investment product development Outperformance by active management will remain very difficult as always I do believe that a studious and disciplined individual investor can outperform by taking advantage of current trends that offer exceptional risk vs reward opportunities However where most will have trouble is knowing when to sit on your hands and do nothing when the environment is no longer favorable If you cannot be patient and only participate in the absolute best opportunities and at the same time be discipline enough to manage risk you should just index and spend your time doing something more productive SPY QQQ IWM DIAblogscfainstituteorginve
